# Git Commit

**Agent does NOT execute `git commit`** – when agent runs commit, Cursor adds "Made-with: Cursor" trailer. Agent only:
1. Stages (`git add .`)
2. Proposes command: `git commit -m "message"`
3. User copies and runs in their terminal

- Never open editor (`git commit` without `-m`)
- No trailers (Signed-off-by, Co-authored-by, Made-with: Cursor, etc.)

# Push – Log Check

**Before push** always check: `git log -3 --format=%B` (last 3 commits).

If any commit contains a trailer (Made-with: Cursor, Co-authored-by: Cursor, etc.) – **push ABSOLUTELY FORBIDDEN**. Do not execute push. Notify user.

Only if log is clean – propose `git push`.

## FORBIDDEN

**NEVER** modify git configuration: `git config`, `core.hooksPath`, `core.*`, etc. Absolutely forbidden.
